## THE ADAPTATION

| Patient model | In.Tune model |
|---|---|
| PATIENT (hub, only writer of ID) | **PARTY** (hub, only writer of party_id) |
| Clinical Encounters (PHI · segregated) | **`sensitive` schema** — SSN/EIN/passport, SAR, privileged notes |
| CRM / Relationship (contributes, not owns) | `crm` — roles, addresses, relationships |
| Financials / GL | `engage` + `bill` — engagements, time, AR |
| ERP / HR Assign. | `core` — user linkage, staff assignment |
| RCM / Refunds (PHI · segregated) | **`sensitive.screening`** — sanctions/PEP results |

The structural rule I'm enforcing: **only `crm.party` mints a party_id.** Every spoke FKs to it. Nothing sensitive lives on the hub. The `sensitive` schema is physically separate with its own RLS, its own access log, its own retention clock, and no grant to the default app role.

